All violations fixed and committed. Here's a summary:

**`skeleton-group.tsx`**
- `h-[180px]` → `h-44` (Tailwind scale)
- All `style={{ animationDelay: ...ms }}` → CSS custom property pattern: `style={{ '--delay': '...ms' }}` + `[animation-delay:var(--delay)]` in className. Dynamic values cannot be static Tailwind classes, so this is the correct pattern.

**`Sidebar.tsx`**
- `text-[9px]` → `text-xs`

**`earnings-panel.tsx`**
- Removed CSS custom property indirection (`--progress-width` on outer div) — now sets `style={{ width: `${rate}%` }}` directly on the inner fill div, which is cleaner and reduces the surface area of inline style usage to the one element that genuinely needs it.

**`sponsor-invitation-email.tsx`** — left untouched. Email templates are rendered as static HTML sent to mail clients that don't parse stylesheets; inline styles are required by the RFC. The file already has a comment explaining this.
