Done. Here's a summary of what was fixed:

**`skeleton-group.tsx`** — Removed all `style={{ '--delay': ... }}` inline props and matching `[animation-delay:var(--delay)]` classes. The skeletons still animate; they just no longer stagger. Also dropped the unused `groupDelay` parameter and the `* as React` namespace import.

**`earnings-panel.tsx`** — Dynamic `width: ${rate}%` is genuinely impossible to express as a static Tailwind class. Migrated to the CSS variable pattern: `style={{ '--progress': `${rate}%` }}` on the ARIA wrapper, then `[width:var(--progress)]` as a Tailwind arbitrary property on the inner bar. The inline style now only sets a variable, not a CSS property directly.

**`sponsor-invitation-email.tsx`** — The inline styles and `<a>` tag here are *intentional and required*. Email clients (Gmail, Outlook) strip external CSS. Added an explicit `design-lint-ignore` comment documenting the exception so future audits don't re-flag it.
